'''Renewable energy in Brunei''' includes the [[photovoltaic]] power generation in [[Brunei]].

==Photovoltaic power==
Brunei opened its first [[solar power plant]], the 1.2 MW [[Tenaga Suria Brunei]] [[photovoltaic power plant]], on 26 May 2011 by [[List of Sultans of Brunei|Sultan]] [[Hassanal Bolkiah]]. The plant powers up around 200 houses in the nation.<ref name="tdworld">{{cite web|url=http://tdworld.com/renewables/brunei-installs-first-photovoltaic-power-station|title=Brunei Installs First Photovoltaic Power Station  |website=Transmission & Distribution World |date=1 June 2011 |accessdate=2014-08-23}}</ref><ref name="sultanate">{{cite web|url=http://www.sultanate.com/news_server/2011/27_may_1.html|title=Sultan opens Brunei's first solar power plant |author=Liza Mohamad  |publisher=sultanate.com |accessdate=2014-08-23}}</ref>

