{{For|the ski resort|Saklıkent}} {{Infobox protected area | name = Saklıkent National Park | alt_name = ''Saklıkent Milli Parkı'' | iucn_category = | photo = Saklıkent Kanyonu (2).jpg | photo_alt = | photo_caption = A view from the canyon. | photo_width = | map = Turkey | map_alt = | map_caption = | map_width = | relief = yes | label = Saklıkent NP | label_position = top | mark = | marker_size = | location = [[Fethiye]], [[Muğla Province]], Turkey | nearest_city = | coords = {{coord|36|28|07.62|N|29|24|12.31|E|region:TR|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | coords_ref = | area = {{convert|1643|ha|abbr=on}} | designation = | authorized = | created = | established = {{start date|1996|06|06}} | designated = | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | visitation_ref = | governing_body = [[Ministry of Forest and Water Management (Turkey)|Ministry of Forest and Water Management]] | administrator = | operator = | owner = | world_heritage_site = | website = {{URL|http://www.milliparklar.gov.tr/mp/saklikent/index.htm}} | child = | embedded = }} '''Saklıkent National Park''' ({{lang-tr|Saklıkent Milli Parkı}})), established on June 6, 1996, is a [[national park]] in southwestern Turkey. The national park is a [[canyon]], and is located in [[Muğla Province]], {{convert|50|km|mi|abbr=on}} far from [[Fethiye]]. Thé Canyon is 65km from Kaş in the Antalya province.
The canyon is {{convert|300|m|ft|abbr=on}} deep and {{convert|18|km|mi|abbr=on}} long, being one of the deepest in the world. It was formed through abrasion of the rocks by flowing waters over thousands of years. As the level of water rises during winter months, visitors can enter the canyon all year around only the deeper parts in the summer. {{convert|4|km|mi|abbr=on}} of the canyon are walkable after April, when most of the snow in the [[Taurus Mountains]] has melted and passed through on its way to the [[Mediterranean Sea]]. Saklıkent means "hidden city" in [[Turkish language|Turkish]]. The full length of 16km is only possible to discover with professional equipment and knowledge of advanced canyoning. Some adventure centers offer guided tours with an overnight Biwak camp and about 30 waterfalls to rappel.
